(-1477307672, -1245650066, 'CHIPIN', '1312694553000mikw_uyma@hotmail.com', 'PENDING', 'COMMENT_READ', 5.00, '2011-08-06 23:22:33', 'Hey all, seeing these moments makes me sad I''m not there in person. But it also makes me happy that you''ve made such a successful marathon without my help. I enjoyed seeing some familiar faces and some new breakout stars. Everyone seemed to get along and mesh well together - I could tell from the commentary. There were a lot of classic moments - Pies were thrown, people declared they were the wind, chicken rulings were made, and so much more, but it''s all coming to a close. I''m glad people have donated so generously to support the Organization for Autism Research, and that they shared their personal experiences with Autism. The community participation is a big part of what makes these mararathons great. I wish I could have donated more for my final donation, but I probably donated too much for my bank account to handle already. If the summer marathon happens again (it better), I''ll try my hardest to come there next year. -Mike P.S. You can throw this in for Bronanassentia'),
